bench.gen

Interface GenSegment

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenBlock, GenDate, GenFile, GenSegmentBase, GenText, GenValue, GenVariable, GenWords

    public interface GenSegment
    Interface for classes that generate XML text based on input template patterns. Input templates are valid XML files with embedded instructions in the format: 
       <?gen.TOKEN PARAM1=val PARAM2=val2... ?>
 
 Specific formats supported are:
   <?gen.value order=XXX modulus=NN ?>
   <?gen.date order=XXX type=TTT start=MM/DD/YYYY ?>
   <?gen.words count=N source=SSS path=PPP ?>
   <?gen.begin count=N context=XXX ?>
   <?gen.end ?>
  where the various parameters (count, etc) are defined within the specific implementation.

    Note that the leading tag string "gen.value " must match as a (case-insensitive) literal, including colon, period and space characters.

    Version:
    TestHarness8.0
    Author:
    Progress Software Inc., all rights reserved.
    See Also:
    GenBlock, GenDate, GenText, GenValue, GenVariable, GenWords

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        boolean initialize(java.lang.String params)
        Initialize the segment with input parameters and/or literal text. If the type of segment == LITERAL, the params string consists of the literal XML text to be inserted. If the segment is VALUE, WORDS or BLOCK the attributes of the embedded processing instruction are passed in. For BLOCK segments, you must then call the parse() method so the block can scan for child segments.
        Parameters:
        params - A list of name=value pairs, with whitespace delimiters, defining the attributes for the segment.
        Returns:
        true if initialization succeeded and segment should be included, false if this segment should be ignored.

      • generate

        java.lang.String generate(long context)
        Create the output XML text for this segment. If this is a block segment, it will recursively generate text from all child segments. If it is a literal segment it simply returns the constant string value. For value segments, the generated key value may or may not depend on the input context value.
        Parameters:
        context - A unique, sequentially ascending number generated by the caller.
        Returns:
        A String containing the generated output for this segment and any child segments.

      • generate

        long generate(long context,
            java.io.OutputStream out)
        Generate the output XML text for this segment into an output stream.
        Parameters:
        context - A unique, sequentially ascending number generated by the caller.
        out - The output stream into which generated text will be written.

      • isA

        boolean isA(int segmentType)
        Determine which kind of segment you have. Current valid segment types include: LITERAL, VALUE, WORDS, BLOCK, DATE and VARIABLE
        Parameters:
        segmentType - An integer representing the enum value for segment type from GenSegment.
        Returns:
        true if the segment type is the correct Segment type, false otherwise.
